WEBVTT

00:01.001 --> 00:02.668
Henry:
<i>My name is henry morgan.</i>

00:02.670 --> 00:05.471
<i>My story is a long one.</i>

00:05.473 --> 00:08.007
<i>Something happened</i>
<i>nearly two centuries ago.</i>

00:08.942 --> 00:11.543
<i>And I was transformed.</i>

00:11.545 --> 00:13.479
<i>My life</i>
<i>is just like yours...</i>

00:13.481 --> 00:16.215
<i>Except for one</i>
<i>small difference...</i>

00:17.550 --> 00:19.918
[ gasps ]
<i>...It never ends.</i>

00:21.221 --> 00:25.557
<i>Over the years, you could say</i>
<i>I've become a student of death.</i>

00:25.559 --> 00:28.827
<i>You see, I need to find a key</i>
<i>to unlock my curse.</i>

00:28.829 --> 00:30.562
<i>So I currently work</i>

00:30.564 --> 00:31.897
<i>For the new york city</i>
<i>medical examiner's office.</i>

00:31.899 --> 00:33.532
It holds the largest collection

00:33.534 --> 00:35.401
<i>Of slightly chilled corpses</i>
<i>in the world.</i>

00:35.403 --> 00:38.637
<i>If your game is death,</i>
<i>you go where the action is.</i>

00:43.343 --> 00:46.845
[ indistinct conversations ]

00:46.847 --> 00:48.814
[ tapping ]

00:55.188 --> 00:58.023
Conrad: The carlyle endowment
is committed

00:58.025 --> 01:01.827
To supporting institutions
that share our core values.

01:01.829 --> 01:03.862
Wouldn't you agree,
mother?

01:03.864 --> 01:06.432
With you, conrad?
I don't think it's possible.

01:06.434 --> 01:07.933
[ sighs ]
of course.

01:07.935 --> 01:10.436
Will anyone be spared
your ire tonight?

01:10.438 --> 01:11.703
Your father.

01:11.705 --> 01:13.939
Lucky for him, he's dead.

01:13.941 --> 01:16.442
Mr. Mayor,
I was under the impression

01:16.444 --> 01:19.411
You communists
didn't care for such opulence.

01:19.413 --> 01:21.914
Your reviews
are pedantic, unoriginal,

01:21.916 --> 01:23.515
Lacking insider clarity.

01:23.517 --> 01:26.919
Fortunately, you're a critic
and completely unimportant.

01:26.921 --> 01:29.788
If only it was
her funeral.

01:35.028 --> 01:37.296
[ indistinct conversations ]

01:39.899 --> 01:42.301
Lance!

01:42.303 --> 01:44.703
I told you to wait.

01:44.705 --> 01:46.872
Mrs. Carlyle,
I hope you're well.

01:46.874 --> 01:49.041
I'm 91 years old.
I'm never well.

01:49.043 --> 01:51.643
I'd say you look
91 years <i>young.</i>

01:51.645 --> 01:53.745
Explain to me again,
director chambers,

01:53.747 --> 01:56.482
Why you haven't finished
the renovation of my gallery.

01:56.484 --> 01:58.250
The gallery
is my top priority.

01:58.252 --> 02:00.486
Disappoint me again
and you'll be curating

02:00.488 --> 02:03.489
Finger-painting exhibitions
for preschoolers.

02:19.405 --> 02:21.540
[ applause in distance ]

02:25.812 --> 02:28.180
Gloria carlyle
was always there

02:28.182 --> 02:30.616
To sustain the museum
with her generosity.

02:30.618 --> 02:32.284
Her vision for this institution

02:32.286 --> 02:36.255
Has seen us
through many dark hours.

02:36.257 --> 02:41.093
Gloria has two great passions --
her family and her art.

02:41.095 --> 02:43.462
It's a great honor
to have them both here with us.

02:43.464 --> 02:46.465
Tonight, on the 60th anniversary
of her endowment,

02:46.467 --> 02:47.866
We celebrate a woman

02:47.868 --> 02:50.636
Who's touched so many
with her kindness.

02:50.638 --> 02:52.171
To gloria.

02:56.309 --> 02:57.309
[ camera shutter clicking ]

02:57.311 --> 02:59.278
[ police radio chatter ]

02:59.280 --> 03:01.146
Man: Detective,
mayor wants to know

03:01.148 --> 03:03.048
When we are releasing
the guests.

03:03.050 --> 03:04.650
The mayor's office
called?

03:04.652 --> 03:06.552
No.
The mayor is here.

03:06.554 --> 03:08.554
Okay. Check the names
against the guest list,

03:08.556 --> 03:10.322
Then get them
out of here.
Got it.

03:10.324 --> 03:12.324
Guess blue bloods bleed
like the rest of us.

03:12.326 --> 03:14.159
[ sighs ]
ready for a high-profile case?

03:14.161 --> 03:15.494
Jo: Give me
the good news first.

03:15.496 --> 03:16.962
[ chuckling ]
I'm fresh out.

03:16.964 --> 03:18.630
This part of the museum's
under construction,

03:18.632 --> 03:19.965
So video surveillance
was down.

03:19.967 --> 03:21.867
Guards were stationed
at the exits,

03:21.869 --> 03:23.168
Didn't tell us much.

03:23.170 --> 03:24.636
And a whole bunch
of muckety-mucks

03:24.638 --> 03:26.505
Came running in her
after they found her.

03:26.507 --> 03:28.807
Csi says they trampled
the whole scene.

03:28.809 --> 03:30.976
So, what's the bad news?
Oh.

03:30.978 --> 03:32.277
Your m.E. Didn't show.

03:36.015 --> 03:37.316
Where's henry?

03:37.318 --> 03:40.152
He, um...
Couldn't make it.

03:41.187 --> 03:43.822
Does he understand
how important this is?

03:43.824 --> 03:45.257
This is gloria carlyle.

03:45.259 --> 03:47.659
There are buildings,
parks, a bridge

03:47.661 --> 03:48.994
All named after her.

03:48.996 --> 03:50.262
The mayor is here.

03:50.264 --> 03:52.030
He's expecting
our best people on this.

03:52.032 --> 03:54.099
Seemed like
something personal.

03:54.101 --> 03:56.535
Although,
you can never tell with him.

03:56.537 --> 03:58.036
But I'm really excited

03:58.038 --> 04:00.372
To be your on-site lead
for this.

04:00.374 --> 04:02.074
[ clears throat ]

04:02.076 --> 04:03.709
Would you -- would you like
to hear my initial report?

04:03.711 --> 04:06.545
Yeah. Okay.
Let's have it.

04:06.547 --> 04:09.114
Well, to begin with...

04:09.116 --> 04:10.782
She's dead.

04:12.952 --> 04:16.588
<i>When gloria carlyle died,</i>

04:16.590 --> 04:21.059
<i>91 years worth of memories</i>
<i>disappeared in an instant.</i>

04:21.061 --> 04:25.063
<i>People, places,</i>
<i>loved ones and enemies alike,</i>

04:25.065 --> 04:28.567
<i>All gone, lost forever.</i>

04:28.569 --> 04:31.403
<i>Even one distant memory of me.</i>

04:31.405 --> 04:35.574
<i>We can only imagine</i>
<i>what her final thoughts were.</i>

04:35.576 --> 04:38.644
<i>Fear, anger --</i>
<i>we'll never know.</i>

04:38.646 --> 04:41.213
<i>Everything is forgotten</i>
<i>in death.</i>

04:41.215 --> 04:44.082
<i>I, of course,</i>
<i>can never forget,</i>

04:44.084 --> 04:46.084
<i>Especially gloria</i>

04:46.086 --> 04:49.354
<i>And the debt I owe her.</i>

04:56.162 --> 04:58.730
Lucas: Broken pelvis,
cracked femur --

04:58.732 --> 05:00.265
Compound fracture there.

05:00.267 --> 05:02.934
The damage to her vertebrae
is extensive.

05:02.936 --> 05:05.937
20 to 30 contusions
on all sides,

05:05.939 --> 05:09.241
Including defensive wounds
on the hands and the forearms.

05:09.243 --> 05:11.743
And that's
just my initial report.

05:11.745 --> 05:13.078
What do you think?

05:13.080 --> 05:14.513
Hello, detective.

05:16.649 --> 05:18.450
I'll let
the adults talk.

05:18.452 --> 05:20.118
Why weren't
you there?

05:20.120 --> 05:22.020
I never go
to <i>that</i> museum.

05:22.022 --> 05:24.456
Henry, what are you
talking about?

05:24.458 --> 05:26.124
Do you have any idea
who she was?

05:26.126 --> 05:27.759
Gloria carlyle,

05:27.761 --> 05:29.828
The last living heir
to john arthur carlyle,

05:29.830 --> 05:31.630
Who founded new york steel
in 1901.

05:31.632 --> 05:34.466
The family's fortune and power
were legendary.

05:34.468 --> 05:36.768
Many claim to have built
new york city.

05:36.770 --> 05:40.272
The carlyle family
did the job.

05:41.941 --> 05:44.710
It's gloria.
Gloria carlyle.

05:47.447 --> 05:49.781
Did you know her?

05:49.783 --> 05:51.283
No.

05:51.285 --> 05:53.552
But I'll find out
what happened.

05:53.554 --> 05:56.154
I'm starting
my autopsy now.

05:56.156 --> 05:58.323
One thing's
for certain --

05:58.325 --> 06:00.792
This wasn't
a natural death.

06:07.166 --> 06:08.567
Hi.

06:08.569 --> 06:09.568
Oh!

06:09.570 --> 06:10.569
Hey. Hi.

06:10.571 --> 06:12.070
Hi back at you.

06:12.072 --> 06:14.172
It's crazy all the reporters
out there, huh?

06:14.174 --> 06:15.841
Yeah.

06:15.843 --> 06:18.377
They're probably just, uh,
here for the carlyle case.

06:18.379 --> 06:21.646
I was -- I was the lead m.E.
At the crime scene there.

06:21.648 --> 06:22.848
Wow.

06:22.850 --> 06:25.684
So, do you think
it was murder?

06:25.686 --> 06:28.720
Well, we just completed
the initial autopsy,

06:28.722 --> 06:30.088
And that was rough.

06:30.090 --> 06:33.091
Still waiting
for the tox report to come back,

06:33.093 --> 06:36.361
But, uh, looks like it.
[ chuckles ]

06:36.363 --> 06:38.263
So, uh,
so what do you -- oh.
[ cellphone vibrating ]

06:38.265 --> 06:41.433
Hey, d-do you want something?
A soda?

06:41.435 --> 06:42.868
My treat.

06:42.870 --> 06:44.002
Oh, no thanks.

06:44.004 --> 06:45.370
Ah, got to take it.

06:45.372 --> 06:47.539
Yeah.
Go -- go take it.

06:47.541 --> 06:50.876
I got the m.E.
On the record.

06:50.878 --> 06:53.145
He says it's murder.

06:58.851 --> 06:59.885
[ bell dings ]

06:59.887 --> 07:01.386
Morning.

07:01.388 --> 07:02.587
You look terrible.

07:02.589 --> 07:03.922
Well, thank you.

07:03.924 --> 07:06.258
Even an immortal
needs a solid six hours.

07:06.260 --> 07:08.727
Well, today might not
be much better.

07:08.729 --> 07:10.362
A lieutenant reece called.

07:10.364 --> 07:13.165
Wondered
if you'd seen this.

07:18.137 --> 07:19.137
What do you need?

07:19.139 --> 07:20.372
Coffee.

07:20.374 --> 07:22.307
Lots of coffee.

07:22.309 --> 07:23.608
Mm.

07:31.284 --> 07:34.419
They say this gloria carlyle
was a real witch.

07:34.421 --> 07:36.955
The most hated blue blood
in the city.

07:38.491 --> 07:40.926
[ indistinct conversations ]

07:40.928 --> 07:43.662
She wasn't always.

07:43.664 --> 07:46.865
You want to talk
about it?

07:54.507 --> 07:58.109
Ah, a louis xiv desk
right out in the open.

07:58.111 --> 07:59.945
Grandfather
must have bought it.

07:59.947 --> 08:01.613
Could you imagine
an estate like this

08:01.615 --> 08:03.114
Coming on the market
all at once?

08:03.116 --> 08:05.250
I bet you
those berkowitz brothers

08:05.252 --> 08:07.285
Will try
to get there first, huh?

08:07.287 --> 08:08.787
Ray and arty berkowitz,

08:08.789 --> 08:10.455
Your nemesi?
Yeah, sure.

08:10.457 --> 08:12.958
They got this tony
upper east side store,

08:12.960 --> 08:15.293
But they'd walk right over
a body for a choice antique.

08:15.295 --> 08:18.797
Mm, well,
I'm sure you can handle it.

08:18.799 --> 08:20.532
I should get
to the station.
Oh, listen.

08:20.534 --> 08:21.933
Um, if at work,
you hear about

08:21.935 --> 08:23.802
The carlyle estate sale,
could you let me know?

08:23.804 --> 08:25.370
Put me on the list?

08:25.372 --> 08:27.706
Abraham, I'm a medical examiner,
an officer of the city.

08:27.708 --> 08:31.276
Don't worry.
I've got other sources.

08:31.278 --> 08:33.712
Conrad: My family has been
part of the heart blood

08:33.714 --> 08:35.981
Of this city
for over 150 years.

08:35.983 --> 08:37.449
And this is the first time

08:37.451 --> 08:39.384
That anything like this
has ever happened.

08:39.386 --> 08:41.653
Very sorry.
Sorry is not good enough.

08:41.655 --> 08:44.623
I was told this autopsy
would be held confidentially.

08:44.625 --> 08:46.391
So, I take it
you were not the one

08:46.393 --> 08:47.626
Who talked to the press.

08:47.628 --> 08:48.894
What happened?

08:48.896 --> 08:50.228
I'm not sure yet.
What can we do about it?

08:50.230 --> 08:51.296
There's nothing to be done
about it now.

08:51.298 --> 08:53.298
This is on page six!

08:53.300 --> 08:54.299
Whoa.

08:54.301 --> 08:57.502
Hey, uh...

08:57.504 --> 08:58.803
I need to talk to you.

08:58.805 --> 09:00.105
You were the source
for the story.

09:00.806 --> 09:04.309
Okay. So, uh...
[ stammers ]

09:04.311 --> 09:05.644
Was she pretty?
Very.

09:06.479 --> 09:09.014
I feel awful, okay?

09:09.016 --> 09:10.849
I-I'm gonna go talk
to the lieutenant.

09:10.851 --> 09:12.918
I've written up
my resignation.

09:12.920 --> 09:15.320
Go back to the lab.
Say nothing.

09:15.322 --> 09:17.656
I was the source for the story.
Do you understand?

09:17.658 --> 09:19.157
Okay.
Thank you.

09:19.159 --> 09:20.725
I-I just -- you know,
I'd been up all night.

09:20.727 --> 09:21.826
And she just appeared.

09:21.828 --> 09:23.328
Stop.
Yeah?

09:23.330 --> 09:25.864
Leave. Try not to make
any more headlines today.

09:25.866 --> 09:27.265
Copy.

09:27.267 --> 09:30.168
What are you
gonna do about it?

09:31.704 --> 09:35.874
Henry, jo,
have a seat, please.

09:35.876 --> 09:37.576
Lieutenant,
I'm afraid an apology

09:37.578 --> 09:39.511
Must be made standing.

09:39.513 --> 09:42.180
Mr. Carlyle, on behalf
of the city of new york

09:42.182 --> 09:44.849
And the office
of the chief medical examiner,

09:44.851 --> 09:46.051
Accept this apology
and the knowledge

09:46.053 --> 09:47.719
This will never
happen again.

09:47.721 --> 09:51.690
I still want him
taken off the case.

09:53.459 --> 09:55.093
But I've apologized.

09:55.095 --> 09:56.861
I've extended my hand
as a gentleman.

09:56.863 --> 10:00.065
My mother deserves the best,
and you have been found lacking.

10:00.067 --> 10:02.867
Mr, carlyle,

10:02.869 --> 10:06.471
No one understands better
the specifics of this case

10:06.473 --> 10:08.740
Or the importance
of the carlyle name.

10:08.742 --> 10:10.742
All due respect, sir,
he is the best.

10:10.744 --> 10:12.811
Shall my lawyers
contact the mayor again,

10:12.813 --> 10:13.945
Twice in one day?

10:15.748 --> 10:17.582
Lieutenant,
if I may --

10:17.584 --> 10:19.718
Henry, I'm sorry, but I'm
pulling you from the case.

10:19.720 --> 10:22.487
Dr. Vaughn
will take over from here.

10:29.161 --> 10:30.629
Hey, hanson.
Yo.

10:30.631 --> 10:32.130
Check the security tapes
the museum just sent over.

10:32.132 --> 10:33.898
The, uh, speeches
from the gala should be on it.

10:33.900 --> 10:35.433
Want butter
on your popcorn?

10:35.435 --> 10:37.902
That's your choice.
I'm going to the crime scene.

10:39.905 --> 10:41.606
Henry, you okay?

10:41.608 --> 10:44.109
I've never been removed
from a case before.

10:44.111 --> 10:46.011
Well,
happens to the best of us.

10:46.013 --> 10:48.580
You know, just because
you don't have a body

10:48.582 --> 10:51.082
Doesn't mean
you can't investigate with me.

10:51.084 --> 10:54.019
Great.
I'll come with you.

10:54.021 --> 10:55.954
There's just one problem.

10:55.956 --> 10:57.555
We're going to the museum.

10:59.625 --> 11:02.293
Wow, you really do
have an issue with this.

11:02.295 --> 11:04.929
So, I guess
the only question is,

11:04.931 --> 11:07.232
How badly do you want to solve
this murder?

11:09.468 --> 11:11.736
Let me grab my scarf.

11:14.807 --> 11:16.775
[ siren wailing ]

11:16.777 --> 11:18.977
Okay. What is it?
Spill it.

11:18.979 --> 11:21.780
You were acting stranger
than normal.

11:21.782 --> 11:23.314
It's nothing.
Come on, henry.

11:23.316 --> 11:25.116
What is your issue
with this museum?

11:25.118 --> 11:26.818
Why don't you
come here?

11:26.820 --> 11:28.319
Old memories.

11:28.321 --> 11:30.155
Okay.
Can I say one thing?

11:30.157 --> 11:33.458
A cop usually knows what's
going on with their partner.

11:33.460 --> 11:34.492
We should talk.

11:34.494 --> 11:35.727
I'm an m.E., jo.

11:35.729 --> 11:37.729
I'm not sure
I'm officially your partner.

11:37.731 --> 11:42.400
I was not making
any official kind of point.

11:42.402 --> 11:45.170
[ thunder rumbles ]

11:45.172 --> 11:48.440
[ woman laughing ]

11:50.843 --> 11:52.744
This way!

11:52.746 --> 11:54.512
Over here!

11:54.514 --> 11:55.914
Quickly.

11:55.916 --> 11:57.682
[ panting ]

11:57.684 --> 12:00.018
We're closed.
I beg your pardon.

12:00.020 --> 12:01.186
It's a private party.

12:01.188 --> 12:04.022
But we're the vermeers.

12:04.024 --> 12:06.257
This is dr. Henry vermeer
and I'm his wife.

12:06.259 --> 12:07.926
We've just arrived
from london

12:07.928 --> 12:10.595
For his great-grandfather's
exhibit.

12:10.597 --> 12:12.197
You're not here, lady.

12:12.199 --> 12:13.932
We've traveled
3,500 miles.

12:13.934 --> 12:16.000
Calm down. I...

12:16.002 --> 12:17.869
Um...

12:17.871 --> 12:20.038
Look,
could you please hurry?

12:20.040 --> 12:21.873
I was the one
that forgot the umbrella

12:21.875 --> 12:24.109
And mrs. Vermeer
hates getting wet.

12:24.111 --> 12:25.443
Fine.

12:25.445 --> 12:27.712
Fine.

12:27.714 --> 12:31.015
[ slow-tempo jazz music plays ]

12:31.017 --> 12:33.118
Abigail,
we're not supposed to be here.

12:33.120 --> 12:35.453
I'm also quite certain
vermeer was dutch.

12:36.689 --> 12:38.189
[ indistinct conversations ]

12:43.395 --> 12:45.029
This is very rash.

12:45.031 --> 12:48.733
You can't plan
for everything, henry.

12:48.735 --> 12:50.769
Sometimes
it's good to be rash.

12:50.771 --> 12:52.303
It's fun.

13:02.548 --> 13:03.982
Jo: Henry?

13:03.984 --> 13:06.317
You okay?

13:06.319 --> 13:08.453
So, the victim was struck
several times

13:08.455 --> 13:10.488
With an unidentified
object.

13:10.490 --> 13:12.724
There were
no weapon found.

13:12.726 --> 13:13.992
Blood splatter
was irregular

13:13.994 --> 13:15.994
With traces
all over the floor.

13:15.996 --> 13:18.096
Hmm.
What do you think?

13:18.098 --> 13:20.465
What I've discovered
is that the scene of any crime

13:20.467 --> 13:22.100
Is much larger
than this space.

13:22.102 --> 13:24.269
To truly understand
this murder,

13:24.271 --> 13:25.770
We must go back
seconds, minutes,

13:25.772 --> 13:26.905
Hours, even.
Henry.

13:26.907 --> 13:28.072
I've been doing this
for 10 years.

13:28.074 --> 13:29.274
Let's go easy
on the lecture.

13:29.276 --> 13:30.942
You asked me
what I thought.

13:30.944 --> 13:32.944
[ sighs ]
my mistake.

13:32.946 --> 13:34.445
Please.

13:34.447 --> 13:37.282
I think we should go back,
walk in gloria's shoes --

13:37.284 --> 13:39.951
Her yves saint laurent pumps,
to be exact.

13:39.953 --> 13:43.121
They look like
fall of '61.

13:43.123 --> 13:44.189
Are you serious?

13:44.191 --> 13:46.691
I know a bit
about women's shoes.

13:47.793 --> 13:50.195
What is that?

13:50.197 --> 13:52.630
It's an original
fbi fingerprinting kit.

13:52.632 --> 13:54.632
Well, the room has already
been dusted, henry,

13:54.634 --> 13:56.100
With actual
modern equipment.

13:56.102 --> 13:58.636
I'm not looking for prints.
I'm after rubber.

13:58.638 --> 14:01.706
The soles of gloria's shoes
were made of natural soft rubber

14:01.708 --> 14:04.142
Harvested from
the amazonian sharinga trees.

14:04.144 --> 14:05.643
They leave a subtle mark

14:05.645 --> 14:07.912
Unlike the synthetic rubber
used in shoes after '73.

14:18.157 --> 14:19.791
Fascinating.

14:39.845 --> 14:40.945
She crawled here.

14:42.414 --> 14:44.082
She crawled?
Yes.

14:44.084 --> 14:46.284
And the marks lead
all the way to...

14:52.157 --> 14:53.992
I know what killed her.

14:53.994 --> 14:55.026
The weapon?

14:55.028 --> 14:56.494
It wasn't a weapon.

14:56.496 --> 14:58.796
It was this
marble staircase.

15:00.266 --> 15:03.268
So, she fell.
It was an accident.

15:03.270 --> 15:04.669
She was pushed.

15:05.771 --> 15:07.605
How do you know
she was pushed?
The crawl.

15:07.607 --> 15:09.707
The damage to her body
was crippling.

15:09.709 --> 15:11.743
Broken pelvis,
countless fractures.

15:11.745 --> 15:13.878
She shouldn't have
been able to move.

15:13.880 --> 15:15.380
But someone made her.

15:15.382 --> 15:17.382
Gloria tried to get away
the only way she could,

15:17.384 --> 15:19.217
By crawling.

15:19.219 --> 15:23.354
She crawled 30 meters
into the gallery,

15:23.356 --> 15:25.390
In agony, in pain.

15:25.392 --> 15:27.859
Why?

15:27.861 --> 15:29.894
There was someone else.

15:29.896 --> 15:32.563
The guard said
gloria was alone.

15:32.565 --> 15:33.464
He was wrong.

15:33.466 --> 15:35.700
I'm not sold.

15:35.702 --> 15:37.468
Very well.
I'll explain it again.

15:37.470 --> 15:39.103
No. Listen.

15:39.105 --> 15:41.205
There's no way of knowing
that there was someone else.

15:41.207 --> 15:43.241
[ cellphone ringing ]

15:43.243 --> 15:44.475
Yep?

15:44.477 --> 15:46.277
Hanson:
There was someone else.

15:47.413 --> 15:49.113
What?

15:49.115 --> 15:50.982
Video surveillance
from the party

15:50.984 --> 15:53.217
Shows a guy
heading toward the east gallery

15:53.219 --> 15:54.919
Just after gloria
wandered off.

15:54.921 --> 15:56.254
He -- he slipped past
the guards.

15:56.256 --> 15:57.655
Okay.
Do we have an I.D.?

15:57.657 --> 15:59.991
Yeah.
One lance sharp.

15:59.993 --> 16:02.093
I.D.'d him from his photo
in the newspaper.

16:02.095 --> 16:03.528
Okay.
Let's bring him in.

16:05.931 --> 16:07.231
Do not gloat, henry.

16:14.139 --> 16:15.974
Lance, fella, you did
pretty well for yourself.

16:15.976 --> 16:18.142
Guy from queens landing himself
an upper east side princess.

16:18.144 --> 16:19.610
What do you think, jo?

16:19.612 --> 16:21.446
You know, part of me thinks,
"attaboy, lance."

16:21.448 --> 16:25.783
The other part of me
wants to stomp your face in.

16:25.785 --> 16:27.518
Before we get to that,

16:27.520 --> 16:30.021
Why'd you kill
gloria carlyle?

16:30.023 --> 16:31.789
I've told you.
I didn't.

16:31.791 --> 16:32.690
I couldn't.

16:32.692 --> 16:34.092
It's on video.

16:34.094 --> 16:35.860
You followed gloria
out of the party.

16:35.862 --> 16:37.362
And when you came back,

16:37.364 --> 16:39.130
<i>You looked shaken,</i>
<i>which makes sense</i>

16:39.132 --> 16:41.599
<i>Because you just killed</i>
<i>a 90-year-old woman.</i>

16:41.601 --> 16:44.302
What are you doing here?

16:44.304 --> 16:47.805
Assisting with the case,
offering a meta-analysis.

16:47.807 --> 16:49.774
I can help,
lieutenant.

16:49.776 --> 16:51.676
So jo keeps
telling me.

16:51.678 --> 16:53.311
May I stay?

16:53.313 --> 16:55.646
How can I tell you to stay?
You're not even here.

16:55.648 --> 16:57.882
I'm sorry.

16:57.884 --> 17:00.318
Are you asking me
to leave or --

17:00.320 --> 17:02.787
Oh, for god sake, henry.
Just watch.

17:02.789 --> 17:04.489
<i>Why would I kill her?</i>

17:04.491 --> 17:06.991
I'm in love
with her granddaughter.

17:06.993 --> 17:08.626
I'm gonna marry sofia.

17:08.628 --> 17:11.996
We have you following the victim
to the scene of the crime.

17:11.998 --> 17:14.499
Conrad wouldn't give me
his blessing.

17:14.501 --> 17:16.501
So I decided
to ask gloria.

17:16.503 --> 17:19.570
All night, I'm getting up
the courage to do it.

17:19.572 --> 17:22.340
When she left the party,
I saw my chance.

17:22.342 --> 17:23.975
Oh, let me guess
what happened next, lance.

17:23.977 --> 17:25.576
She said no,
you pushed her down the steps,

17:25.578 --> 17:27.245
And then you stole this.

17:27.247 --> 17:31.516
A 6-carat blue diamond
worth $3 million.

17:31.518 --> 17:33.751
Found it at your loft.

17:33.753 --> 17:35.686
Gloria gave that to me
for the engagement.

17:35.688 --> 17:38.356
Oh, she gave you
a $3 million ring?

17:38.358 --> 17:40.324
I know.
It sounds crazy.

17:40.326 --> 17:42.260
<i>She gave me the ring</i>

17:42.262 --> 17:44.762
<i>And then she mumbled something</i>
<i>about following your heart.</i>

17:44.764 --> 17:47.432
<i>She'd never said anything</i>
<i>like that to me before.</i>
<i>May I borrow your phone?</i>

17:47.434 --> 17:49.500
<i>That's the last</i>
<i>I saw of her, I swear.</i>

17:49.502 --> 17:52.203
<i>This is the biggest fairy tale</i>
<i>I've ever heard.</i>

17:52.205 --> 17:55.606
[ cellphone ringing ]

17:57.876 --> 17:59.544
Lieutenant?

17:59.546 --> 18:02.780
Henry, what are you doing?

18:02.782 --> 18:04.282
No.

18:04.284 --> 18:05.716
No, actually,

18:05.718 --> 18:08.186
This is not better
than just barging in.

18:08.188 --> 18:09.921
Hold on.

18:09.923 --> 18:12.557
Why was gloria mumbling?

18:12.559 --> 18:13.958
I don't know.

18:13.960 --> 18:17.228
She was acting strange,
slurring her words.

18:17.230 --> 18:19.864
What did her skin
feel like?
Cold.

18:19.866 --> 18:21.966
Was she, uh --
was she sweating?

18:23.735 --> 18:25.903
Did she lean
on her cane?
Yeah.

18:25.905 --> 18:27.905
Are you done?

18:27.907 --> 18:29.207
Great.

18:29.209 --> 18:30.741
Goodbye.

18:30.743 --> 18:33.144
She also said something
about a burning smell

18:33.146 --> 18:35.480
Like...Toast.

18:35.482 --> 18:36.781
[ banging on glass ]

18:39.918 --> 18:41.252
What is it?

18:41.254 --> 18:42.720
She may not
have been pushed.

18:42.722 --> 18:44.622
Wait, what are you saying?
You were wrong?

18:44.624 --> 18:46.124
No. We need
to go back further.

18:46.126 --> 18:47.758
Okay, I don't want
a lecture here,

18:47.760 --> 18:49.060
But what does that mean?

18:49.062 --> 18:50.461
The burning smell
was phantosmia.

18:50.463 --> 18:52.630
It's a symptom of a stroke
in the temporal lobe.

18:52.632 --> 18:54.765
It's very rare and usually
caused by medication,

18:54.767 --> 18:56.667
Something
for a neurological condition --

18:56.669 --> 18:58.669
Epilepsy, parkinson's.

18:58.671 --> 19:01.305
But I found no sign of either
in my autopsy.

19:01.307 --> 19:02.607
Her brain was normal.

19:02.609 --> 19:04.008
What do you want to do?

19:04.010 --> 19:05.943
I need a biopsy
of gloria's liver.

19:05.945 --> 19:08.179
Then we can tell
exactly what poisoned her.

19:08.181 --> 19:09.847
It's not your body,
henry.

19:09.849 --> 19:11.849
Only the acting m.E.
Can do that.

19:11.851 --> 19:14.152
I know someone
who can do it for me.

19:16.188 --> 19:19.457
Henry, I-I-I'm so sorry
I got you kicked off the case.

19:19.459 --> 19:21.692
I need a liver biopsy
for gloria carlyle.

19:21.694 --> 19:23.861
She's not here.
The -- the body's gone.

19:23.863 --> 19:25.796
Dr. Vaughn released her
to the mortuary.
What?

19:25.798 --> 19:27.265
Wait.
What's going on?

19:27.267 --> 19:29.634
An innocent man is
about to be arrested for murder.

19:29.636 --> 19:33.104
I-I'll do anything
to fix this.

19:33.106 --> 19:34.639
Just tell me.

19:34.641 --> 19:38.609
There's nothing you <i>can</i> do.

19:38.611 --> 19:40.878
Sofia: I can't help you,
detective martinez.

19:40.880 --> 19:42.713
Lance didn't kill
my grandmother.

19:42.715 --> 19:44.448
Sofia,
the best way to help lance

19:44.450 --> 19:45.483
Is by talking to me.

19:45.485 --> 19:46.817
What do you
want to know?

19:46.819 --> 19:48.352
Your grandmother's
medication.

19:48.354 --> 19:49.987
If we knew
what she was taking,

19:49.989 --> 19:52.156
We may be able to figure out
what killed her.

19:52.158 --> 19:53.658
I don't know
anything about that.

19:53.660 --> 19:54.959
Your father might.

19:54.961 --> 19:56.827
Do you think
he would help us?
No.

19:56.829 --> 19:58.496
Not if lance
could benefit.

19:58.498 --> 19:59.830
I-I don't get it.

19:59.832 --> 20:01.232
Somebody murdered
your grandmother.

20:01.234 --> 20:03.501
Don't you want to find out
who really killed her?

20:03.503 --> 20:06.504
He doesn't care.
He didn't love her.

20:06.506 --> 20:08.039
You don't understand
my family.

20:08.041 --> 20:10.041
We're not like
normal people.

20:10.043 --> 20:11.676
Instead of having
lives of our own,

20:11.678 --> 20:13.678
We learned how to hurt
each other for sport.

20:13.680 --> 20:16.080
My grandmother
was a heartless woman,

20:16.082 --> 20:18.549
At least
as long as I knew her.

20:24.756 --> 20:26.324
This is amazing.

20:26.326 --> 20:28.259
To be alone with them.

20:28.261 --> 20:30.161
Like an artist.

20:30.163 --> 20:32.730
Woman:
She's very beautiful.

20:35.334 --> 20:36.534
Yes.

20:36.536 --> 20:38.202
Yes, she is.

20:38.204 --> 20:39.537
I saw you arrive.

20:39.539 --> 20:42.039
It's good to see
people in love.

20:42.041 --> 20:44.175
And yet I'm confused.

20:44.177 --> 20:45.876
You don't have a ring
on your finger.

20:45.878 --> 20:47.278
Neither does she.

20:47.280 --> 20:48.512
Why haven't you
asked her to marry you?

20:48.514 --> 20:51.716
Excuse me.
Who are you?

20:51.718 --> 20:53.951
My question first.

20:53.953 --> 20:55.419
Uh, champagne?

20:55.421 --> 20:57.688
Never drink
and you never lose your head.

20:57.690 --> 20:58.789
Now, why?

21:03.762 --> 21:05.796
I don't think
I'm the right man for her.

21:05.798 --> 21:08.199
Nothing in life is certain,
especially this.

21:08.201 --> 21:09.800
It's a long story.
When you're in love,

21:09.802 --> 21:12.903
You feel like you have
all the time in the world.

21:12.905 --> 21:15.072
But trust me,
you don't.

21:15.074 --> 21:20.378
If you have a chance at love,
mr. Vermeer, take it.

21:22.414 --> 21:26.250
It's gloria.
Gloria carlyle.

21:26.252 --> 21:28.552
You're crashing my party.

21:35.227 --> 21:37.828
Jo: Guess what I learned
about gloria.

21:37.830 --> 21:40.164
Gloria threatened to kick conrad
out of the will.

21:40.166 --> 21:41.932
That's motive.
Yeah. There's more.

21:41.934 --> 21:43.934
His lawyers went after
the probate judge.

21:43.936 --> 21:46.404
They managed to wrest control
of everything in the townhouse.

21:46.406 --> 21:48.606
He's having an estate sale
right now.

21:48.608 --> 21:50.274
Now?
We should go.

21:50.276 --> 21:51.509
I-it's invite only.

21:51.511 --> 21:53.744
[ sighs ]
can I borrow your phone?

21:54.846 --> 21:57.415
[ dialing ]

21:57.417 --> 21:59.283
[ ringing ]

21:59.285 --> 22:00.751
Abe. It's me.

22:00.753 --> 22:02.086
The carlyle estate sale
is today.

22:02.088 --> 22:03.287
Think you can make it?

22:03.289 --> 22:04.455
I'm already there.

22:04.457 --> 22:05.923
You're there?

22:05.925 --> 22:08.125
In the flesh.
Told you I have my sources.

22:08.127 --> 22:09.760
Excellent.

22:09.762 --> 22:12.463
Now, I need you
to do me a favor.

22:12.465 --> 22:14.598
Can you get
to gloria carlyle's bathroom?

22:14.600 --> 22:16.767
Oh, henry,
what are we talking about here?

22:16.769 --> 22:19.637
I built a very respectable
reputation over the years,

22:19.639 --> 22:21.038
Unlike those berkowitzes.

22:21.040 --> 22:22.973
We heard that.

22:22.975 --> 22:24.175
Yeah, good.

22:24.177 --> 22:26.110
Abe, you're
all I've got here.

22:26.112 --> 22:27.545
All right.
All right.

22:27.547 --> 22:28.946
Henry,
what is it you need?

22:28.948 --> 22:30.548
I need you
to take a picture

22:30.550 --> 22:33.284
Of all the medications
in gloria's medicine cabinet.

22:33.286 --> 22:35.820
Now, bear with me,
this is technical.

22:35.822 --> 22:39.056
I need you to take
a j-p-g on your smartphone

22:39.058 --> 22:40.891
And then mail that
to jo's computer.

22:40.893 --> 22:43.094
Henry, I'm on it.

23:05.016 --> 23:07.785
[ door opens, closes ]

23:13.925 --> 23:17.495
[ door opens, closes ]

23:29.541 --> 23:32.176
Ooh, that's nice.

23:32.178 --> 23:34.178
Unh-unh.
Bathroom.

23:51.096 --> 23:53.030
Bingo.

23:53.032 --> 23:55.566
You know
I figured it out, right?

23:55.568 --> 23:57.902
I know
your secret, henry.

23:57.904 --> 24:01.038
Your whole issue
with the museum.

24:01.040 --> 24:02.873
You're a modern-art guy.

24:02.875 --> 24:05.075
Trust me,
I'm a classicist.

24:05.077 --> 24:06.811
All right.
Now I'm really confused.

24:06.813 --> 24:08.179
You gonna keep me guessing?

24:10.615 --> 24:12.283
It reminds me of someone.

24:13.952 --> 24:15.052
Who?

24:17.255 --> 24:19.657
Come on, henry.
I'm an nypd detective.

24:19.659 --> 24:21.759
I'm gonna get a name
out of you.

24:21.761 --> 24:23.727
Trust me,
time is on my side.

24:23.729 --> 24:27.264
You'll find with me, jo,
that's not usually the case.

24:27.266 --> 24:28.566
[ computer chimes ]

24:28.568 --> 24:30.835
Hey,
we got abe's pictures.

24:34.406 --> 24:35.940
[ keys clacking ]
no.

24:35.942 --> 24:37.608
No.

24:37.610 --> 24:40.277
For the heart.
For the lungs.

24:40.279 --> 24:42.847
Blood pressure.

24:42.849 --> 24:45.282
It's not here.

24:45.284 --> 24:47.117
What's not here?
The toxin.

24:47.119 --> 24:48.686
None of these medications

24:48.688 --> 24:51.121
Would have caused a stroke
in the temporal lobe.

24:51.123 --> 24:53.824
[ sighs ]

24:53.826 --> 24:56.093
What do we do now?

24:56.095 --> 24:58.128
Well, we have no suspect,
no poison.

24:58.130 --> 24:59.330
We're nowhere, henry.

24:59.332 --> 25:01.265
The lawyers
are gonna take over.

25:01.267 --> 25:03.801
First, the medical examiner
blabs to the press.

25:03.803 --> 25:05.803
Now you're dragging
your heels.

25:05.805 --> 25:07.137
You have your suspect.

25:07.139 --> 25:09.206
Indict him.

25:09.208 --> 25:12.276
My family
has endured enough.

25:12.278 --> 25:14.445
He has epilepsy.

25:14.447 --> 25:15.779
What?

25:15.781 --> 25:17.681
H-henry, wait, wait.

25:19.150 --> 25:20.317
Mr. Carlyle.

25:20.319 --> 25:21.785
What is he doing here?

25:21.787 --> 25:23.487
I thought he was removed
from the case.

25:23.489 --> 25:25.122
What do you take
for your epilepsy?

25:25.124 --> 25:27.324
What?
The medication.
Is it phenytoin?

25:27.326 --> 25:30.327
Or some other anticonvulsant?
I don't have to answer that.

25:30.329 --> 25:32.329
What is this?
Dr. Morgan,
this is not the time.

25:32.331 --> 25:33.731
Okay, h-henry,
let's go.

25:33.733 --> 25:35.900
This is important.
The case depends on it.

25:35.902 --> 25:37.668
Do you take phenytoin?

25:37.670 --> 25:39.904
Yes, millions of people do.
Why are you asking me this?

25:39.906 --> 25:41.639
Because it's the drug
that killed your mother.

25:49.214 --> 25:51.181
Are we really doing this?
Questioning conrad carlyle?

25:51.183 --> 25:53.584
He's one of the most powerful
people in the whole city.

25:53.586 --> 25:55.753
Yeah, it's risky,
but the will gives him motive.

25:55.755 --> 25:58.088
The prescription, the means.
We have to talk to him.

25:58.090 --> 26:00.591
What do you want to do,
boss?

26:00.593 --> 26:01.959
Bring him in.

26:04.696 --> 26:07.031
Jo: Mr. Carlyle,
how would you characterize

26:07.033 --> 26:08.432
Your relationship
with your mother?

26:08.434 --> 26:09.533
<i>Conflicted.</i>

26:09.535 --> 26:11.869
I'm not here.

26:11.871 --> 26:13.537
No, you are not.

26:13.539 --> 26:15.539
Jo: <i>Did your mother</i>
<i>threaten to take you</i>

26:15.541 --> 26:17.274
<i>Out of the will?</i>
<i>Often.</i>

26:17.276 --> 26:19.710
But I always managed
to get myself written back in.

26:19.712 --> 26:20.811
Not this time.

26:23.048 --> 26:24.615
You were not
in the will?

26:24.617 --> 26:26.050
<i>I know my mother,</i>
<i>detective.</i>

26:26.052 --> 26:27.851
<i>When she threatened</i>
<i>to write me out,</i>

26:27.853 --> 26:29.286
<i>It meant that</i>
<i>she'd already done it.</i>

26:29.288 --> 26:31.555
Of all the people
who wanted her to live,

26:31.557 --> 26:32.890
I had the most to gain.

26:32.892 --> 26:34.558
There goes his motive.

26:34.560 --> 26:36.060
<i>I hated my mother.</i>

26:36.062 --> 26:37.628
<i>But I did not</i>
<i>kill her.</i>

26:37.630 --> 26:39.063
<i>She was a miserable</i>
<i>old woman.</i>

26:39.065 --> 26:40.464
<i>Most of new york</i>
<i>hated her.</i>

26:40.466 --> 26:41.865
<i>Who knows</i>
<i>how she got that way?</i>

26:41.867 --> 26:43.767
Henry: What is it?

26:43.769 --> 26:46.604
This room is filled
with degas, monet,

26:46.606 --> 26:48.405
All masterpieces.

26:48.407 --> 26:51.475
And one painting
by an unknown argentinean.

26:51.477 --> 26:54.878
Ah, the vermeers.

26:56.982 --> 26:59.416
Abigail,
this is gloria.

26:59.418 --> 27:00.918
It's her party.

27:00.920 --> 27:04.054
I think you have
someone special here, abigail.

27:04.056 --> 27:05.389
I think
you're right.

27:05.391 --> 27:06.557
[ sighs ]

27:06.559 --> 27:07.825
Do you have
someone special?

27:07.827 --> 27:11.462
Yes.
Yes, I do.

27:12.764 --> 27:14.999
Unfortunately,
he couldn't be here tonight.

27:15.001 --> 27:16.100
Conrad: Mother.

27:16.102 --> 27:18.002
Mother!

27:19.170 --> 27:23.741
Daddy says it's time to go.
We have to go, now.

27:23.743 --> 27:25.442
Well, good night.

27:25.444 --> 27:27.111
They tell me
it stopped raining.

27:27.113 --> 27:29.613
Should be
a beautiful evening.

27:29.615 --> 27:31.015
Let's go, conrad.

27:37.522 --> 27:39.957
Man: <i>Unless you have anything</i>
<i>of substance here,</i>

27:39.959 --> 27:41.692
<i>This conversation</i>
<i>is over.</i>

27:43.628 --> 27:45.429
[ elevator bell dings ]

27:45.431 --> 27:47.131
It's not all bad.

27:47.133 --> 27:48.799
We know the type of drug
that poisoned gloria.

27:48.801 --> 27:50.134
That's something.

27:50.136 --> 27:51.869
And conrad's argument's
hardly an alibi.

27:51.871 --> 27:53.937
Henry, we have your guess.
That's it.

27:53.939 --> 27:55.439
There's no tox report.

27:55.441 --> 27:57.541
We still need proof
the drug was in her system,

27:57.543 --> 27:59.643
What it was,
and when she was poisoned.

27:59.645 --> 28:01.345
And we don't have
her body.

28:02.981 --> 28:04.114
Lucas.
Yes?

28:04.116 --> 28:05.649
Hey! Hi.

28:05.651 --> 28:08.385
What did you do?

28:08.387 --> 28:10.654
Okay.

28:10.656 --> 28:11.989
Before I tell you,

28:11.991 --> 28:13.791
I'd really prefer
you don't get mad.

28:13.793 --> 28:15.059
What's happening?

28:15.061 --> 28:16.994
Lucas took
a long lunch.

28:16.996 --> 28:20.664
Lucas never takes a lunch
longer than half an hour,

28:20.666 --> 28:23.333
Enough time to enjoy
exactly one comic book.

28:23.335 --> 28:24.835
It's a graphic novel.

28:24.837 --> 28:26.370
He's also wearing
his metrocard lanyard,

28:26.372 --> 28:28.038
Which he usually hangs

28:28.040 --> 28:30.374
On the light behind his work
station until he leaves at 8:00.

28:32.343 --> 28:34.511
Where did you go, lucas?

28:34.513 --> 28:35.846
[ chuckles ]

28:35.848 --> 28:38.348
I went
to the funeral home

28:38.350 --> 28:40.751
And did a biopsy
on gloria carlyle's liver.

28:40.753 --> 28:42.820
Wait, what?!

28:42.822 --> 28:43.821
How?

28:43.823 --> 28:45.689
I told them dr. Vaughn

28:45.691 --> 28:48.992
Left his wedding ring
inside the body

28:48.994 --> 28:52.096
And I had to...
Retrieve it.

28:52.098 --> 28:53.530
Okay, h-h-hold on.

28:53.532 --> 28:55.866
You went to a funeral home --
hey!

28:55.868 --> 28:58.102
Yeah.
...Did an unauthorized exam
on a person

28:58.104 --> 29:00.370
About to be buried
on your lunch break?

29:00.372 --> 29:01.939
This was all my fault,
all right?

29:01.941 --> 29:03.207
I'm trying to fix this.

29:03.209 --> 29:04.708
Wow, you are pretty
when you're mad.

29:04.710 --> 29:06.310
Henry: Lucas?
Yes?

29:10.215 --> 29:12.216
It's the best thing
you've ever done.

29:12.218 --> 29:14.885
Oh. That's probably
the first real compliment

29:14.887 --> 29:17.054
You've ever given --
not now.
We've got work to do.

29:17.056 --> 29:18.589
Yeah, okay.
Mm-hmm.

29:18.591 --> 29:21.892
Okay. For the record,
I did not hear any of this.

29:21.894 --> 29:23.160
Got it.

29:26.464 --> 29:28.065
I was right.

29:28.067 --> 29:29.600
It was phenytoin --
three times the usual does.

29:29.602 --> 29:31.602
But she wasn't poisoned
at the party.

29:31.604 --> 29:33.604
Based on the damage
to her liver,

29:33.606 --> 29:35.572
It was taken
three hours earlier.

29:35.574 --> 29:37.574
Who was with gloria
before she left?

29:37.576 --> 29:39.143
That's the killer.

29:39.145 --> 29:41.745
Conrad wasn't there.
Neither was lance or sofia.

29:41.747 --> 29:43.113
Just the nurse, marta.

29:43.115 --> 29:45.449
Jo, they read the will.

29:45.451 --> 29:48.318
The nurse
got everything.

29:55.560 --> 29:57.094
[ door opens ]

29:57.096 --> 29:58.962
Marta,
I'm detective hanson.

29:58.964 --> 30:00.497
You know why you're here?

30:00.499 --> 30:02.599
<i>This is about</i>
<i>the money.</i>

30:02.601 --> 30:05.068
Know what happens
if she's charged with murder?

30:05.070 --> 30:06.937
The family lawyers
contest the will

30:06.939 --> 30:08.772
And the money
goes back to them.

30:08.774 --> 30:12.276
<i>Marta, gloria carlyle</i>
<i>was poisoned</i>

30:12.278 --> 30:13.944
With phenytoin.

30:13.946 --> 30:16.246
You were in charge of her
medications, weren't you?

30:16.248 --> 30:18.749
Yes.
But I would never hurt her.

30:18.751 --> 30:21.084
I was her nurse
for 20 years.

30:21.086 --> 30:24.521
How'd she treat you?
Poorly at first.

30:24.523 --> 30:26.356
She was old, angry,

30:26.358 --> 30:28.959
But someone
had to take care of her.

30:28.961 --> 30:30.794
<i>No one else would.</i>

30:30.796 --> 30:33.130
<i>Marta, take me through</i>

30:33.132 --> 30:35.966
The night gloria died,
step by step.

30:35.968 --> 30:39.436
It was like any other.
Dinner was served at 5:00.

30:39.438 --> 30:42.673
I helped dress her for the party
at half past.

30:42.675 --> 30:45.309
She was cold,
so I made her a fire.

30:45.311 --> 30:46.877
A fire?

30:46.879 --> 30:48.812
<i>While she was dressing...</i>
<i>The sun was still out.</i>

30:48.814 --> 30:50.380
It was warm, mid-80s.

30:50.382 --> 30:52.983
A fire would have been
unbearable.

30:52.985 --> 30:55.552
Something doesn't fit.
We have to go there.

30:55.554 --> 30:57.487
Conrad's not gonna
let us in.

30:57.489 --> 31:00.090
It's not his anymore.

31:01.159 --> 31:03.694
Ray: Be careful
with those boxes.

31:03.696 --> 31:06.730
Man: You got it,
mr. Berkowitz.

31:06.732 --> 31:09.733
Excuse me.
Who are you?

31:09.735 --> 31:11.501
Um, detective martinez,
nypd.

31:11.503 --> 31:13.337
Where's gloria carlyle's
bedroom?

31:13.339 --> 31:15.739
Upstairs.
Master suite.

31:15.741 --> 31:16.506
Great.

31:16.508 --> 31:18.942
Touch nothing!

31:22.146 --> 31:24.314
Marta said gloria
was cold.

31:24.316 --> 31:25.682
She wanted a fire.

31:25.684 --> 31:28.018
Older people
get cold, henry.

31:28.020 --> 31:32.055
I think there
was another reason.

31:46.838 --> 31:48.872
People do that?
They burn letters?

31:48.874 --> 31:51.008
I've only seen that
in old movies.

31:51.010 --> 31:53.076
Those movies weren't old
to gloria.

31:57.382 --> 32:00.717
This room is filled
with degas, monet,

32:00.719 --> 32:02.085
All masterpieces.

32:02.087 --> 32:06.123
And one painting
by an unknown argentinean.

32:11.296 --> 32:13.297
Arty!

32:13.299 --> 32:15.399
Damn it!
This isn't a complete set.

32:15.401 --> 32:17.401
There's only 23
champagne glasses.

32:17.403 --> 32:18.635
We're missing one.

32:18.637 --> 32:20.570
The list was checked
only a week ago.

32:20.572 --> 32:22.706
Look.
"complete set."

32:22.708 --> 32:24.908
Never drink
and you never lose your head.

32:24.910 --> 32:26.910
She never drank.

32:26.912 --> 32:30.247
These are vintage
coupe glasses,

32:30.249 --> 32:32.049
Her personal set.

32:32.051 --> 32:34.051
Were they stored here?
Yeah.

32:34.053 --> 32:35.652
You know your glassware.

32:35.654 --> 32:38.488
If you ever have a, uh, case
with interesting antiques,

32:38.490 --> 32:39.756
Call me.

32:39.758 --> 32:41.658
We're not afraid
of dead bodies.

32:41.660 --> 32:43.894
We'll step
right over them.

32:45.096 --> 32:46.763
What are you thinking?

32:46.765 --> 32:49.099
She never drank,
yet there's one glass missing.

32:49.101 --> 32:50.801
Marta's story
doesn't make sense.

32:50.803 --> 32:53.070
Okay, ray.
I'll check the dinner plates.

32:53.072 --> 32:55.072
Dinner.

32:55.074 --> 32:57.107
Jo, I know
this is annoying,

32:57.109 --> 32:59.609
But can I please borrow
your phone?

32:59.611 --> 33:01.345
Marta, I don't care
where you're from,

33:01.347 --> 33:03.347
What kind of troubles you had
back in the home country.

33:03.349 --> 33:05.615
My questions
are only gonna get tougher here.

33:05.617 --> 33:08.018
[ cellphone ringing ]

33:08.020 --> 33:09.519
What is it?

33:09.521 --> 33:11.121
Oh, no. I'm not --

33:11.123 --> 33:14.024
H-henry, I'm --

33:14.026 --> 33:16.293
What did gloria
have for dinner?

33:16.295 --> 33:17.461
Duck confit.

33:17.463 --> 33:18.628
Duck confit.

33:18.630 --> 33:20.297
[ sighs ]

33:20.299 --> 33:24.768
A traditional
gascony confit?

33:24.770 --> 33:26.470
Yes.
Yeah, traditional.

33:26.472 --> 33:28.438
Don't call me again,
henry.

33:29.974 --> 33:32.676
It didn't happen here.
She was given the drug later.

33:32.678 --> 33:34.311
What about
the liver sample?

33:34.313 --> 33:36.146
Duck confit's
incredibly salty.

33:36.148 --> 33:37.547
The sodium in her system

33:37.549 --> 33:39.649
Would have accelerated
the drug's effect.

33:39.651 --> 33:42.719
The time of poisoning was wrong
by 30 minutes, maybe an hour.

33:42.721 --> 33:44.654
So, she was killed
before the gala.

33:44.656 --> 33:45.655
Let's check the car.

33:45.657 --> 33:46.656
Let's go.

33:46.658 --> 33:47.657
Excuse me.

33:47.659 --> 33:49.159
What are you
doing here?

33:49.161 --> 33:51.294
Our job, sir.
Asking questions.

33:51.296 --> 33:53.663
This home belongs
to the carlyle endowment.

33:53.665 --> 33:54.831
I want you both out.

33:54.833 --> 33:56.500
Why?

33:56.502 --> 33:58.568
Why do you not want us
to find your mother's killer?

33:58.570 --> 34:00.737
You have marta.
Indict her.

34:00.739 --> 34:03.006
By the time I'm done,
you'll be solving crimes

34:03.008 --> 34:04.841
In the port authority
bus station.

34:04.843 --> 34:06.209
Sir, I suggest you file

34:06.211 --> 34:07.644
A formal complaint
with my lieutenant.

34:07.646 --> 34:09.813
Consider it done.

34:09.815 --> 34:12.749
Lieutenant reece,
this is conrad carlyle.

34:12.751 --> 34:15.585
I'm calling
about two of your people.

34:23.995 --> 34:28.165
[ sighs ]
1965 rolls-royce phantom v.

34:28.167 --> 34:29.833
Everyone should have
one of these.

34:29.835 --> 34:35.038
Scottish leather.
Maple inlays.

34:35.040 --> 34:37.274
Discreet bar.

34:44.182 --> 34:46.716
Murder weapon included.

34:46.718 --> 34:48.952
This is where
it happened.

34:48.954 --> 34:51.054
Who was in this limo
with gloria?

34:51.056 --> 34:54.124
Conrad, sofia, marta --
one of them killed her.

34:59.530 --> 35:02.799
Jo, you don't
have to call anyone.

35:02.801 --> 35:04.301
I know who did it.

35:08.139 --> 35:09.739
Lieutenant reece,

35:09.741 --> 35:12.709
I want an explanation
for this.

35:12.711 --> 35:14.711
That's why we're here.

35:14.713 --> 35:16.079
Who killed my mother?

35:16.081 --> 35:17.447
Henry: Gloria did.

35:19.817 --> 35:20.984
It was suicide?

35:20.986 --> 35:22.152
My autopsy revealed

35:22.154 --> 35:23.920
A woman
with months to live.

35:23.922 --> 35:26.590
Gloria knew this,
so she planned her own death,

35:26.592 --> 35:28.158
Down to the last detail --

35:28.160 --> 35:30.760
When she would take the drug
that would kill her,

35:30.762 --> 35:33.096
How much time
she would have after that.

35:33.098 --> 35:35.132
She chose
the night of the gala

35:35.134 --> 35:38.168
Because it was a celebration
of her favorite place

35:38.170 --> 35:40.003
And her one chance
to tell everyone

35:40.005 --> 35:41.771
Exactly what she thought
of them.

35:41.773 --> 35:43.607
The party
was her suicide note.

35:43.609 --> 35:45.942
She left the gala
knowing she only had

35:45.944 --> 35:47.577
A few moments to live.

35:47.579 --> 35:49.813
But she was held up
by lance.

35:49.815 --> 35:52.315
The drug was acting
too fast now.

35:52.317 --> 35:55.218
When she came to the stairs,
she fell.

35:56.587 --> 35:58.488
And here was my mistake.

35:58.490 --> 36:00.290
I couldn't imagine her

36:00.292 --> 36:02.292
Dragging herself
across the floor,

36:02.294 --> 36:04.961
30 meters,
in pain few could imagine.

36:04.963 --> 36:07.297
I thought only fear
could drive someone to do that.

36:07.299 --> 36:09.633
Henry, you're lecturing.

36:09.635 --> 36:11.468
Why did she do it?

36:11.470 --> 36:12.669
Because there was
another reason.

36:14.138 --> 36:16.339
There was a letter
in gloria's fireplace,

36:16.341 --> 36:18.141
Burned the night she died.

36:18.143 --> 36:19.509
It was signed f.C.

36:19.511 --> 36:21.978
This room is filled
with degas, monet,

36:21.980 --> 36:23.146
All masterpieces.

36:23.148 --> 36:24.848
What doesn't belong here?

36:27.318 --> 36:28.785
This.

36:30.621 --> 36:33.223
A painting
by an unknown artist.

36:35.159 --> 36:36.826
In the 1950s,

36:36.828 --> 36:39.296
Fernando costa was
a young painter on the rise --

36:39.298 --> 36:41.498
Promising, but hardly worthy
of this museum.

36:41.500 --> 36:44.501
Only one person
could make this happen.

36:44.503 --> 36:46.536
Gloria carlyle.

36:46.538 --> 36:49.005
And she was in love
with him.

36:49.007 --> 36:50.407
Do you have
someone special?

36:50.409 --> 36:52.175
Yes, I do.

36:52.177 --> 36:54.110
Unfortunately,
he couldn't be here tonight.

36:55.846 --> 36:58.215
This theory
is based on...Love.

36:58.217 --> 37:01.184
We do have proof,
correct?

37:01.186 --> 37:04.487
[ sighs ]
mr. Carlyle?

37:04.489 --> 37:05.989
My father told me once

37:05.991 --> 37:08.692
How she'd fallen in love
with an artist.

37:08.694 --> 37:11.695
He told me
how he'd found out

37:11.697 --> 37:15.765
And threatened to ruin
this young painter.

37:15.767 --> 37:18.201
And mother relented
and stayed.

37:18.203 --> 37:21.371
Father took pride
in having won her back.

37:21.373 --> 37:25.041
He said it was just a dalliance
that she'd forgotten.

37:25.043 --> 37:27.043
But he was wrong.

37:27.045 --> 37:30.480
She never forgave him.

37:33.618 --> 37:35.585
And I never forgave her.

37:43.060 --> 37:44.628
She donated
millions of dollars

37:44.630 --> 37:46.196
To secretly keep
this painting

37:46.198 --> 37:47.731
On display...

37:47.733 --> 37:51.201
And one day die
in front of it.

37:51.203 --> 37:53.303
I hope she saw it.

38:08.986 --> 38:11.321
Good work back there.

38:11.323 --> 38:12.722
Thank you.

38:12.724 --> 38:14.824
You know,
I know it's hard

38:14.826 --> 38:17.460
To go someplace
with old memories.

38:17.462 --> 38:18.662
You do?

38:18.664 --> 38:20.130
Yeah.

38:20.132 --> 38:21.731
Yeah, my husband and I,

38:21.733 --> 38:24.401
We used to have this spot
in chinatown.

38:24.403 --> 38:27.671
Best dim sum
in the city.

38:27.673 --> 38:31.141
After he died,
I went back exactly one time.

38:32.610 --> 38:33.977
The good memories,

38:33.979 --> 38:35.312
Those are the ones
that hurt the most.

38:39.917 --> 38:42.018
[ sighs ]

38:42.020 --> 38:44.521
Her name was abigail.

38:46.590 --> 38:48.325
And there you go.

38:48.327 --> 38:50.527
We're talking,
getting to know each other.

38:50.529 --> 38:52.028
Good.

38:52.030 --> 38:54.297
Now I have
a serious question.

38:54.299 --> 38:56.766
Yankees or mets?

38:56.768 --> 38:59.269
More of a cricket man.

38:59.271 --> 39:02.305
Let's go, partner.

39:02.307 --> 39:03.506
[ chuckles ]

39:04.642 --> 39:07.310
Abe: So, the nurse
got everything, huh?

39:07.312 --> 39:08.311
Amazing.

39:08.313 --> 39:09.646
Well, not exactly.

39:09.648 --> 39:11.047
Most of the money
went to the museum

39:11.049 --> 39:12.615
And a handful
of charities.

39:12.617 --> 39:16.119
Marta was left
with a paltry $22 million.

39:16.121 --> 39:17.620
Chump change.

39:17.622 --> 39:19.222
And the family?

39:19.224 --> 39:20.657
Well, none will starve.

39:20.659 --> 39:22.625
The furniture and the ring
will keep them wealthy

39:22.627 --> 39:24.828
For years to come.

39:24.830 --> 39:28.398
I think gloria saw her fortune
as a curse of sorts,

39:28.400 --> 39:30.700
The thing
that kept her from love.

39:30.702 --> 39:32.168
 the rich man like all
hmm.

39:32.170 --> 39:33.303
Ruined her life.

39:33.305 --> 39:34.671
Sad story, indeed.

39:34.673 --> 39:36.239
 oh, lord

39:36.241 --> 39:37.741
 will be judged at that time
I don't know.

39:37.743 --> 39:40.043
In her last moments,
she was with the man she loved.

39:40.045 --> 39:41.311
Mm.

39:41.313 --> 39:42.812
It's a sad story
with a happy ending.

39:42.814 --> 39:45.014
I guess I'll understand that
when I'm older.

39:45.016 --> 39:48.084
 it won't save

39:48.086 --> 39:49.853
Think I'll go
for a stroll.

39:49.855 --> 39:52.188
 oh, won't save

39:52.190 --> 39:53.690
 your poor wicked soul
checkmate, by the way.

39:53.692 --> 39:57.827
Well done...Sir.

39:57.829 --> 40:00.029
 oh, no, it won't save
oh, yeah.
Take your coat.

40:00.031 --> 40:02.298
I don't want to see you,
uh, catch your death.

40:03.000 --> 40:04.667
Eh, eh, eh, eh.
Wait a minute.

40:04.669 --> 40:07.437
 your poor wicked soul
where did you get this?

40:07.439 --> 40:09.105
Tell me the truth.
Are you in communication

40:09.107 --> 40:10.774
With one or more
of the berkowitz brothers?

40:10.776 --> 40:14.010
Because I forbid that.

40:14.012 --> 40:15.245
Ah.

40:15.247 --> 40:17.180
Better.

40:17.182 --> 40:18.648
[ bell dings ]

40:21.051 --> 40:24.020
Henry: <i>For the dead,</i>
<i>all is forgotten.</i>

40:24.022 --> 40:28.725
<i>But all is not lost because</i>
<i>they're remembered by us.</i>

40:28.727 --> 40:32.529
<i>Some we think of fondly,</i>
<i>others less so.</i>

40:32.531 --> 40:35.732
<i>A few are remembered by many,</i>

40:35.734 --> 40:38.401
<i>And some by only a few.</i>

40:38.403 --> 40:41.271
 the very thought of you

40:41.273 --> 40:45.208
 makes my heart sing

40:45.210 --> 40:49.412
 like an April breeze

40:49.414 --> 40:53.783
 I give myself
in sweet surrender 
promise me we'll never be like
gloria and her husband,

40:53.785 --> 40:56.319
That we'll always love
each other.

40:56.321 --> 40:58.721
Oh, never like them.
Of course.

40:58.723 --> 41:01.057
 my one and only love
[ chuckles ]
my henry.

41:01.059 --> 41:03.726
Someday I'll be gone
and you'll still be here.

41:05.429 --> 41:08.598
Abigail...

41:08.600 --> 41:10.667
This may be rash...

41:15.105 --> 41:17.774
I don't know
what the future holds.

41:17.776 --> 41:19.309
But as long
as I'm alive...

41:19.311 --> 41:21.277
 I give myself
in sweet surrender 

41:21.279 --> 41:22.745
...I will always love you.

41:24.081 --> 41:25.682
Forever.

41:25.684 --> 41:28.284
Will you marry me?

41:28.286 --> 41:33.523
 my one and only

41:33.525 --> 41:40.230
 love
